 codes, typically for authentication or confirmation purposes,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as a four, six or eight-digit personal identification number (PIN)."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"PIN code input is presented as a series of individual input fields or boxes, each representing a single digit, to enhance readability and encourage accurate input,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"while supporting smooth keyboard navigation and secured input masking if needed."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput"}}}